import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';
---
<BlogPostLayout
  title="How to play as Pavium - Halo Wars 2"
  description="Master Pavium in Halo Wars 2 with this guide covering Burnout economy boosts, Mega Turrets, Wraith Invaders, and the powerful Lich Vanguard ultimate."
  category="Guides"
  publishedDate="Published on January 31, 2026"
  dateIso="2026-01-31"
  ogImage="/img/HW-Guides/Pavium.jpg"
  youtubeId="SGDnowC0iqc"
  tags={['Halo Wars 2']}
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Pavium is one of the last leaders added to Halo Wars 2. He's a very defensive leader, best suited for players who prefer a defensive playstyle.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">Pros</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Pavium Hero Unit's Drone</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Heals buildings constantly</li>
    <li>Can save you during attacks</li>
    <li>Exploit: Lock Pavium in base without deploying him, and the drone still heals during attacks</li>
    <li>Can heal allies' bases and buildings too</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Johnson Combo</strong>: Put Pavium in a bunker - the drone heals the bunker</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Lich Vanguard Ultimate</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Essentially a flying Scarab</li>
    <li>Fires a beam almost identical to the Scarab's main cannon</li>
    <li>Creates a bubble that allows you to train units on the field</li>
    <li>Best units to train: Wraiths, Reavers (if facing air), Hunters</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Mega Turrets</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Fire almost across the entire map</li>
    <li>Devastating before enemies even reach your base</li>
    <li>Great on maps like Sentry</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Burnout Ability</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Boosts economy for supply and power production</li>
    <li>Speeds up unit production from buildings</li>
    <li>Can be used on teammates' bases</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Cons</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Extremely Weak Overall</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Probably the weakest Banished leader</li>
    <li>One of the weakest leaders in the game overall</li>
    <li>Only leaders possibly weaker are Isabel and Anders</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Mega Turret Drawbacks</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Cost stacks over time (very expensive after 2-3 turrets)</li>
    <li>Takes up base building slots</li>
    <li>Can cripple your economy if not careful</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">No Unique Units</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Only unique unit is the Wraith Invader</li>
    <li>All other units are vanilla Banished units</li>
    <li>Not as distinctive as leaders like Yap Yap</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Poor for 1v1</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Terrible in one-on-one matches</li>
    <li>Works best complementing a stronger leader like Atriox</li>
    <li>Should only play in Team War or other team modes</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Build Order</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Starting Decision</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Choose Burnout over Mega Turrets first</strong></li>
    <li>You don't need Mega Turrets right away</li>
    <li>Consider Mega Turrets as second or third point</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Burnout Placement Strategy</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Build placement matters with Burnout</li>
    <li>For supply boost: Build two Harvesters next to each other</li>
    <li>For mixed boost: Build a Harvester and Power Extractor together</li>
    <li>For separate control: Harvesters on one side, Power Extractors on the other</li>
    <li>Fifth pad should be War Council, Raid Camp, or another Harvester (don't burn just one pad)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Burnout Tips</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Does NOT speed up Harvester upgrades</li>
    <li>DOES speed up tech upgrades and unit production</li>
    <li>Always use Burnout when it's available</li>
    <li>Controller trick: Hit left on D-pad to center on base, then select Burnout to hit all four pads</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Second Tech</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Get Shield Generator</li>
    <li>Build a Foundry for Marauders</li>
    <li>Army composition depends on map, opponents, and teammates</li>
    <li>Pavium has no unique second tech units</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Leader Points Progression</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">First Point</strong>: Burnout 1</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Second Point</strong>: Burnout 2 (bigger radius, more pads)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Third Point Options</strong>:
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2">
        <li>Rain of Fire (spinning Glassing Beam - combos with Voridus's Maelstrom or Johnson's EMP Mac)</li>
        <li>Wraith Invaders (unique unit)</li>
        <li>Avoid Orbital Designator (worst choice)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Fourth/Fifth Point</strong>: Lich Vanguard (flying Scarab ultimate)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Wraith Invaders</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Usage</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Pavium's only unique unit</li>
    <li>Similar concept to Jerome's Mastodons and Arbiter's Phantoms</li>
    <li>Upgrade improves defense and attack, NOT carrying capacity</li>
    <li>Has a siphon-like cannon that attacks ground, infantry, and air</li>
    <li>Units inside are protected when the Wraith takes damage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Best Units to Carry</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hunters (2-3 per Wraith Invader)</li>
    <li>Elite Rangers (weaker, no shields, 3 per squad)</li>
    <li>Ratio: 2-3 Hunters per 1 Elite Ranger squad</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Mega Turrets</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">When to Build</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Not appropriate for every map</li>
    <li>Highway: Not a good map for Mega Turrets</li>
    <li>Sentry: Great map for Mega Turrets</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Optimization</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Don't mix regular turrets and Mega Turrets on the same base</li>
    <li>Add more Shield Generators to protect expensive Mega Turrets</li>
    <li>Add Sensor Towers for increased line of sight</li>
    <li>Combos well with Johnson's Remote Sensors upgrade</li>
    <li>Power Nodes help Mega Turrets gain line of sight</li>
    <li>Orbital Designator can give line of sight for specific spots</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Upgrades</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Lingering Death</strong>: Continued damage after impact</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Compound Detonators</strong>: Increased damage on impact</li>
    <li>You can get both upgrades</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Team Synergies</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Johnson Combo</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Johnson's Remote Sensors + Pavium's Mega Turrets = Insane line of sight coverage</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Support Role</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Pavium works best supporting stronger leaders</li>
    <li>Use Burnout on teammates who are struggling</li>
    <li>Drone can heal ally bases</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Additional Powers</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Enduring Will</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Large healing radius</li>
    <li>Slow healing rate</li>
    <li>Good for entire armies or bases</li>
    <li>Upgradeable three times</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Pavium's Stand</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Like Atriox's Unbreakable but for structures only</li>
    <li>Makes all structures invincible for a short time</li>
    <li>Great when under heavy attack</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Pavium is a defensive specialist who excels at protecting bases and supporting teammates. Use Burnout constantly, be strategic with Mega Turret placement, and leverage the Wraith Invaders for mobile infantry protection. He's not recommended for 1v1 but shines in team games where he can complement aggressive leaders.
  </p>
</BlogPostLayout>
